* Newly introduced atom types for central C of arginine (CAG), aromatic C of tyrosine (CAB) 
* and aromatic C of para-cresol (CG2R6B)
* NBFIX parameters for cation-pi interactions (CHARMM36m-NBF) 
* between toluene/para-cresol/3-methyl-indole and NH4/Gua/TMA
* also for phenylalanine/tyrosine/tryptophan-lysine/arginine
* NBFIX parameters for salt-bridge interactions (CHARMM36m-SBF)
* between NH4/Gua-acetate
* also for lysine/arginine-Glutamic/Aspartic acid
*

!references
!
!Han Liu, Haohao Fu, Xueguang Shao, Wensheng Cai, and Christophe Chipot.
!"Accurate Description of Cation-pi interactions in proteins with a Nonpolarizable Force
!Field at No Additional Cost"  J. Chem. Theory Comput. 2020, 16, 6397-6407
!Han Liu, Haohao Fu, Christophe Chipot, Xueguang Shao, and Wensheng Cai.
!"Accuracy of Alternate Nonpolarizable Force Fields for the Determination of Protein¨CLigand 
!Binding Affinities Dominated by Cation-pi interactions"  J. Chem. Theory Comput. 2021, 17, 3908-3915
!Han Liu, Haohao Fu, Christophe Chipot, Xueguang Shao, and Wensheng Cai.
!"Accurate Description of Solvent-Exposed Salt Bridges with a Non-polarizable 
!Force Field Incorporating Solvent Effects"  J. Chem. Inf. Model. 2022, 62, 3863¨C3873

ATOMS
MASS  -1  CAG       12.01100 ! central C,ARG
MASS  -1  CAB       12.01100 ! aromatic C,TYR
MASS  -1  CG2R6B    12.01100 ! aromatic C,para-cresol

